1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,650
Agent HQ OS is a public scaffold for AI coding agents: memory, validation, review, and telemetry.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:11,650
Without shared memory, each new agent session starts cold and repeats old mistakes.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:19,649
Each run begins with session boot, known failures, validated patterns, and patch history.

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:27,649
Clone it, create the demo workspace, and run validation locally. No credentials required.

5
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:35,649
Higher-risk actions wait behind human review instead of pretending to be production autonomy.

6
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:44,649
The task is done only when checks pass and evidence is visible.

7
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:51,649
Successes and failures are written back so the next session starts smarter.

8
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:59,649
Clone it, run the demo, and copy the starter kit into your own repo.
